    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "2a3bd7c42c5330b4",
      "text": "**Supply chain tracking (provisioning)** is profoundly important, even though a relatively small proportion of organisations do this. Any organisation that trades, or furnishes the material needs of a community (food, care, clothing, accommodation . . personal proitective equipment, vaccines . .) needs tools for supply-chain and value-chain tracking. Some radical means for this are in the pipeline: not a day too soon. The corporations of post-Fordism have a head start on us.\n\n\n"
    },
